{"id":"2305.03115","submitter":"Andreas Amann","authors":"Christopher P. J. O'Connor, Sebastian Wieczorek, Andreas Amann","title":"Loxodromes in Open Multi-Section Lasers","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.107.053520","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.optics math-ph math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We introduce a formalism to efficiently calculate lasing modes and optical\npower flow in multi-section lasers with open boundaries. The formalism is\nunderpinned by a projection of the complex-valued electric field and its\nspatial derivative onto a suitably extended complex $\\mathcal{Z}$-plane, to\nreduce the order of the problem and simplify analysis. In a single-section\nlaser, we show that a laser mode is a loxodrome on the extended complex\n$\\mathcal{Z}$-plane. In a multi-section laser, we obtain loxodromes for\nindividual sections of the laser. Then, a multi-section mode is constructed by\ncontinuously concatenating individual loxodromes from each section using the\nopen boundary conditions. A natural visualization of this construction is given\nby stereographic projection of the extended complex $\\mathcal{Z}$-plane onto\nthe Riemann sphere. Our formalism simplifies analysis of lasing modes in open\nmulti-section lasers and provides new insight into the mode geometry and\ndegeneracy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 May 2023 19:17:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-07"}
