 correlation of the classical activity\nindicators with the RVs. For solar-type stars, $\\Delta\\alpha B^2$ therefore\nrepresents the best simultaneous activity proxy known to date.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 May 2023 13:26:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-17"}
