ble time-periodically pulsating solutions\nof the nonlinear (asymptotic) model exist for all sufficiently small forcing\namplitudes. The existence of such states is formulated as a fixed point problem\nfor the Poincar\\'e return map, and the existence of a fixed point makes use of\nour (constant mass constrained) exponential time-decay estimates of the\nlinearized problem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 May 2023 14:20:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 14 May 2023 04:49:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-16"}
